# Skill: Research Python Coding

## Required in every script
- argparse with --help strings for every argument
- logging module (not print statements)
- pathlib for all file paths
- if __name__ == "__main__": guard
- docstring on every function

## Experiment scripts must also include
- Seed setting: random, numpy, torch
- Result saving to results/tables/{experiment_name}.json
- wandb or local CSV logging

## Evaluation scripts
- Compute CER, WER, DER in the same script
- DER formula:
  diacritic_chars = [c for c in text if unicodedata.combining(c)]
  DER = edit_distance(pred_diacritics, gt_diacritics) / len(gt_diacritics)
- Output a results dict with model name, metric values, timestamp

## Yorùbá-specific
- Always use unicodedata.normalize('NFC', text) before comparison
- Character dictionary path: data/processed/dictionary/yoruba_dict.txt
- Diacritic characters to track: ẹ ọ ṣ + combining grave/acute/macron

## Never
- Hardcode file paths
- Use os.path (use pathlib)
- Commit results to the repo without the generating script
